OL,7,FWhen they received her medical records
OL,8,Fand saw that she was taking HRT, they
OL,9,Ftold Neal that she wasn't covered.
OL,11,FHe said: "We didn't believe HRT was a
OL,12,Fpre-existing condition that had to be
OL,13,Fdeclared. Had we declared HRT, they
OL,14,Fwould have insured us as we understand
OL,15,Fit at no extra cost, just on a
OL,16,Fdifferent type of insurance policy, so
OL,17,Fit's a bit of a loop hole that they're
OL,18,Ftrying to use to get out of paying
OL,19,Fthis large bill."
