OL,7,FThe couple have even complained to the
OL,8,FOmbudsman, who has ruled in favour of
OL,9,Fthe insurance company.
OL,11,FIn a letter sent to them, seen by ITV
OL,12,FNews, the Ombudsman wrote: "I've taken
OL,13,Fon board the point that Mr and Mrs D
OL,14,Fmay have ended up with a similarly
OL,15,Fbranded travel insurance policy (...)
OL,16,Fhowever, I don't think that matters."
OL,18,FHe added that it was reasonable to
OL,19,Fexpect IPA to refund the premium paid
OL,20,Ffor the policy - #36.45.
